2822	\begin{lemma}[Transport of a presentation along a colimit-preserving functor]
2823	  \label{lem:presentation_map_mathlib}
2824	  \lean{SheafOfModules.Presentation.map}
2825	  \mathlibok
2826	  \textit{Provided by Mathlib (\texttt{Mathlib.Algebra.Category.ModuleCat.Sheaf.Quasicoherent}).}
2827	  Let \(F\) be a functor between categories of sheaves of modules that preserves colimits and is
2828	  equipped with an isomorphism \(\eta : F(\mathrm{unit}_R) \cong \mathrm{unit}_S\) sending the unit
2829	  sheaf to the unit sheaf. Then any presentation \(P : \mathrm{Presentation}\,M\) (a
2830	  cokernel-of-free-modules description) induces a presentation
2831	  \(P.\mathrm{map}\,F\,\eta : \mathrm{Presentation}\,(F(M))\) of the image. Applied to the pullback
2832	  and restriction functors (\cref{lem:modules_pullback_mathlib},
2833	  \cref{lem:modules_restrictFunctor_mathlib}), it is how a presentation of \(M\) over one site is
2834	  carried to a presentation over another.
2835	\end{lemma}
