3536	\begin{proof}
3537	  \uses{lem:isIso_fromTildeΓ_presentationPullback, lem:over_restrict_iso,
3538	    lem:over_restrict_pullback_iso, lem:presentation_map_mathlib,
3539	    lem:quasicoherentData_bind_mathlib, lem:modules_pullback_mathlib,
3540	    lem:isIso_fromTildeΓ_of_presentation_mathlib, lem:isLocalization_basicOpen_mathlib,
3541	    lem:exists_finite_basicOpen_cover_le_quasicoherentData,
3542	    def:over_restrict_presentation, def:presentation_pullback_iota_of_quasicoherentData}
3543	  The quasi-coherence datum supplies a presentation
3544	  \(q.\mathrm{presentation}\,i : (M.\mathrm{over}\,(q.X_i)).\mathrm{Presentation}\) on the slice over
3545	  \(q.X_i\). Restrict it along the inclusion of opens \(D(r) \subseteq q.X_i\) by transporting across
3546	  the iterated Grothendieck slice — the template is \(\mathrm{QuasicoherentData.bind}\)
3547	  (\cref{lem:quasicoherentData_bind_mathlib}) — using \(\mathrm{Presentation.map}\)
3548	  (\cref{lem:presentation_map_mathlib}) along the colimit-preserving slice functor; this yields a
